# StockSignal AI

Stock movement prediction system combining PyTorch LSTM with FinBERT sentiment analysis to forecast 5-day price direction across 7 major equities.

---

## Results

- Test Accuracy: **62.07%**
- Random Baseline: 50%
- Academic Benchmark: 52-56%
- Training Data: 7 stocks, 5 years
- Features: 12 technical indicators per timestep

---

## Key Finding

For high-volatility stocks like TSLA, the model learned that technical indicators carry more predictive weight than news sentiment — consistent with the buy the rumor, sell the news phenomenon observed in financial markets.

---

## Architecture

yfinance fetches 5 years of daily price data. 12 technical features are calculated per day including Close, Volume, MA7, MA30, RSI, MACD, StochRSI, Bollinger Bands, and Volume MAs. FinBERT analyzes current news headlines and returns a sentiment score. Features are normalized and formed into 20-day sliding window sequences. A 2-layer PyTorch LSTM (64 to 32 units) outputs direction and confidence score. Predictions are logged to SQLite and served via FastAPI.

---

## Model Performance By Ticker

- NVDA: 64.7%
- GOOGL: 63.3%
- MSFT: 62.1%
- META: 61.9%
- AAPL: 61.2%
- AMZN: 60.8%
- TSLA: 58.4%

---

## Stack

- ML: PyTorch, Hugging Face Transformers (FinBERT), scikit-learn
- Data: yfinance, ta (technical analysis library)
- API: FastAPI + SQLite
- Frontend: Streamlit + Plotly
- Deployment: Docker + docker-compose
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions

---

## Features

- Signal tab: run prediction on any of 7 tickers with live 3-month price chart
- Scan All tab: analyze all 7 tickers simultaneously with ranked confidence
- History tab: view all past predictions with signal distribution chart
- Backtest tab: per-ticker accuracy vs random baseline and academic benchmark

---

## Run With Docker

Clone the repository and generate the model first:

    python pipeline.py

Then run both services:

    docker-compose up --build

FastAPI runs at http://localhost:8000/docs
Streamlit runs at http://localhost:8501

---

## Run Locally

    python -m venv .venv
    .venv\Scripts\activate
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    pip install torch==2.5.1 --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu

    python pipeline.py

    uvicorn app:app --reload
    streamlit run streamlit_app.py

---

## API Endpoints

- GET /health — health check
- POST /predict — body: {"ticker": "AAPL"} — returns direction, confidence, sentiment
- GET /predictions — all past predictions
- GET /predictions/{ticker} — predictions filtered by ticker

---

## Project Structure

    stock-predictor/
    ├── stock_data.py         StockData class — yfinance + technical indicators
    ├── sentiment.py          SentimentAnalyzer class — FinBERT
    ├── model.py              LSTMModel — PyTorch 2-layer LSTM
    ├── pipeline.py           Training pipeline — data prep, sequences, training
    ├── database.py           Database class — SQLite predictions logging
    ├── app.py                FastAPI endpoints
    ├── streamlit_app.py      Streamlit dashboard — 4 tabs
    ├── Dockerfile
    ├── Dockerfile.streamlit
    ├── docker-compose.yml
    └── .github/workflows/ci.yml

